    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 🧼 7. Programmatic Column Standardization (Schema Cleaning)\n",
        "To build a clean analytics catalog, column names must follow standard database design rules. We remove leading or trailing whitespaces, convert names to lowercase, and replace internal whitespaces with snake_case delimiters."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FO7AOaQI2Hmt"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "# CELL 14: COLUMN SCHEMATIC RE-ENGINEERING\n",
        "# Why: Ensure clean column nomenclature and remove processing errors caused by hidden characters.\n",
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Original Column Headers:\", df.columns.tolist())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Vectorized structural cleaning of data frame boundaries\n",
        "df.columns = df.columns.str.strip().str.lower().str.replace(' ', '_').str.replace(r'[^\\w]', '', regex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Standardized Column Headers:\", df.columns.tolist())"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "mg_lD4hU2JPF",
        "outputId": "fcf3c9d5-ddbc-4f1b-9b9c-4b75983890ab"
      },
      "execution_count": 8,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Original Column Headers: ['show_id', 'type', 'title', 'director', 'cast', 'country', 'date_added', 'release_year', 'rating', 'duration', 'listed_in', 'description']\n",
            "Standardized Column Headers: ['show_id', 'type', 'title', 'director', 'cast', 'country', 'date_added', 'release_year', 'rating', 'duration', 'listed_in', 'description']\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 🔡 8. Text Normalization and Categorical Value Harmonization\n",
        "Text features often contain inconsistent formats (e.g., mismatched casing, trailing whitespaces, varied string patterns). We clean these text strings to prevent duplicate categories during analysis."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yPtqHcz_2M0t"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "# CELL 16: TEXT CORRECTION & ENFORCEMENT\n",
        "# Why: Harmonize unstructured text blocks to prevent logical category fragmenting.\n",
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "\n",
        "# Standardize core operational types\n",
        "df['type'] = df['type'].astype(str).str.strip().str.title()\n",
        "print(\"Unique Platform Types:\", df['type'].unique())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Clean high-cardinality metadata fields\n",
        "text_cols = ['title', 'director', 'cast', 'country', 'rating', 'duration', 'listed_in', 'description']\n",
        "for col in text_cols:\n",
        "    if col in df.columns:\n",
        "        df[col] = df[col].astype(str).str.strip()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Correct systemic placeholder variants to uniform NaN tokens\n",
        "df.replace(['nan', 'NaN', 'None', 'null', ''], np.nan, inplace=True)\n",
        "print(\"[SUCCESS] String components standardized. Empty markers replaced with systemic NaN objects.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Rp-aYnKb2O3U",
        "outputId": "afa38545-1c6c-4f5b-b902-445c5b0b46bc"
      },
      "execution_count": 9,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Unique Platform Types: ['Movie' 'Tv Show']\n",
            "[SUCCESS] String components standardized. Empty markers replaced with systemic NaN objects.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 🛠️ 9. Missing Data Imputation & Structural Adjustments\n",
        "Based on our previous missingness diagnostics, we apply targeted treatments:\n",
        "1. High-missingness fields (`director`, `cast`, `country`) are filled with `'Unknown'`.\n",
        "2. Low-missingness critical fields (`date_added`, `rating`, `duration`) are dropped using standard data-cleaning drop rules."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tJhGHrAQ2RlQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "# CELL 18: TARGETED SYSTEM IMPUTATION\n",
        "# Why: Retain maximum data structure without injecting bias into high-missingness variables.\n",
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fill high-missingness fields with placeholder labels\n",
        "df['director'] = df['director'].fillna('Unknown')\n",
        "df['cast'] = df['cast'].fillna('Unknown')\n",
        "df['country'] = df['country'].fillna('Unknown')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop missing rows for low-missingness critical fields\n",
        "initial_row_count = len(df)\n",
        "df.dropna(subset=['date_added', 'rating', 'duration'], inplace=True)\n",
        "rows_dropped = initial_row_count - len(df)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"[IMPUTATION COMPLETE] Categorized categorical missing vectors as 'Unknown'.\")\n",
        "print(f\"[ACTION] Dropped {rows_dropped} rows containing unrecoverable missing features.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "-2wANr8Z2Tty",
        "outputId": "fa6cbbbc-c3b6-4292-e5f5-85503d0a6465"
      },
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "[IMPUTATION COMPLETE] Categorized categorical missing vectors as 'Unknown'.\n",
            "[ACTION] Dropped 17 rows containing unrecoverable missing features.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 📅 10. Temporal Feature Parsing & Type Correction\n",
        "The `date_added` attribute is currently stored as an unstructured string. We parse this column into a proper `datetime64[ns]` timestamp. We then standardize dates into an ISO-compliant `YYYY-MM-DD` format to make date-based filtering smoother."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uqGYcT-i2V-y"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "# CELL 20: TEMPORAL MATRIX HARMONIZATION\n",
        "# Why: Convert object text timestamps to native python datetimes to enable time-series exploration.\n",
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Sample raw dates before conversion:\\n\", df['date_added'].head(2))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Vectorized strip and string parsing transformation\n",
        "df['date_added'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date_added'].str.strip(), format='%B %d, %Y', errors='coerce')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop cases that fail to parse successfully\n",
        "unparsed_dates = df['date_added'].isnull().sum()\n",
        "if unparsed_dates > 0:\n",
        "    df.dropna(subset=['date_added'], inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate consistent representation parameters\n",
        "df['date_added_clean'] = df['date_added'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nSample clean dates post conversion:\\n\", df[['date_added', 'date_added_clean']].head(2))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "aJsLy6D-2X7_",
        "outputId": "0ecd908f-470e-473b-893e-06cb6ac16503"
