            "Sample clean dates post conversion:\n",
            "   date_added date_added_clean\n",
            "0 2021-09-25       2021-09-25\n",
            "1 2021-09-24       2021-09-24\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 🔢 11. Type Casting & Outlier Check\n",
        "We verify that numeric columns match their expected analytical types. For example, `release_year` must be an explicit integer vector, and we perform data quality validation checks to identify any impossible future dates or extreme outliers."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T9pbNOZL2fJK"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "# CELL 22: TYPE INTEGRITY VALIDATION & BOUNDARY CHECKS\n",
        "# Why: Confirm mathematical parameters conform to physical real-world boundaries.\n",
        "# ==========================================\n",
        "\n",
        "# Cast logical column types explicitly\n",
        "df['release_year'] = df['release_year'].astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Detect anomalous records or extreme temporal outliers\n",
        "current_year = 2026\n",
        "future_anomalies = df[df['release_year'] > current_year]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Logical Outlier Bounds Validation Check: Found {len(future_anomalies)} anomalies.\")\n",
        "if len(future_anomalies) > 0:\n",
        "    df = df[df['release_year'] <= current_year]\n",
        "    print(f\"[ACTION] Cleaned anomalies outside logical scope boundaries.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"[SUCCESS] Data schema types validated and locked.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "HmeHnAEV2g6J",
